# Why Binary Matters in Java

Binary is the foundation for:

- Bitwise operators
- HashMap bucket calculation
- Integer storage
- JVM internals
- Network protocols
- File formats
- Cryptography

---

# AI Engineering Connection

Binary is also important in AI.

Examples:

- INT8 model quantization
- FP16 computation
- GPU memory optimization
- Tensor operations
- Image encoding
- Audio encoding

Understanding binary helps explain why optimized AI models use less memory and run faster.

